critique: This document is an executive order that amends a previous executive order regarding the members of the Federal Alcohol Control Administration. It primarily deals with the appointment of specific individuals to this administration. Given the limited scope and focus on personnel, assessing its impact across the seven axes is challenging, as it doesn't directly address issues like immigration, civil liberties, or economic regulation. The most relevant axes would be executive power and potentially economic regulation, although the latter is only indirectly related through the administration's role in alcohol control.
